                            <comment id="16320450" author="sergey_beryozkin" created="Wed, 10 Jan 2018 15:36:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Makes sense to collapse it into a single list at the http transport level&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16321863" author="ffang" created="Thu, 11 Jan 2018 08:38:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;OK, thanks!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16323764" author="sergey_beryozkin" created="Fri, 12 Jan 2018 09:51:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Freeman&lt;br/&gt;
Thanks, I forgot that at the transport level it was already a map, and the problem was indeed due to the fact the JAX-RS code was only checking a &quot;list.get(0)&quot;. It has always worked because multiple accept values have always been set in a single Accept header, I&apos;ve never seen more than one Accept header &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;. &lt;br/&gt;
I guess the fix at the transport level is still OK, given that Accept header is checked in a couple of places, so collapsing the values every time would be a bit time consuming...&lt;br/&gt;
Thanks, Sergey&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16323848" author="ffang" created="Fri, 12 Jan 2018 11:36:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Sergey,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;No problem, just some rare use case I run into. And this is team work, as always!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Freeman&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
